<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gartha</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-05 11:44:00</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Bought this thing at 7th level, and went out to swat gnolls with it.  Got mighty perturbed when the most damage it would do was 19 points.  So, I put it in the bank for a while.  Brought it back out at 11th level, and smacked a lego for 29, slowly but consistently.  I figure if I stow it until 20th, then take it out of storage again, I should be able to utilize it's 17 damage rating to it's full potential.  Until then, the damage cap turns this into a 14 damage weapon, rather than 17.  So for those of you who are looking for a good 2hb for before 10th level, save your money, and buy a much cheaper weapon with lower delay, and a damage rating of 9, which is where you are capped until 10th.  RTS was my choice, 15 pp for a weapon with lower delay (much) +5 hp and +5 mana, and the same damage, AND is magical.  Now, at 15th, I'm using a BFH.  Slow, but effective.</font></td></tr></table>
